                        	<img class="titlebar" src="http://www.sologoodness.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Awsome-lemon-poppy-seed-loaf1.jpg" alt="Gluten Free Lemon &#038; Poppy" /> 
                        </div>             
                        
		   
                
        

		<div class="page-content">
			<div class="row mbf clearfix">
            
            	
  					                    
                  	<p><strong>Awesome Gluten Free Lemon &amp; Poppy Seed Loaf</strong></p>
<p>An everyday cake with real style, sophistication and great taste. You can omit the poppy seeds, although this would be a real shame.</p>
<p>Yields: 1 loaf / Total Time: 60 min / Prep Time: 10 min / Cook Time: 50 min / Oven Temp: 350</p>
<p>Ingredients</p>
<ul>
<li>125 grams of Solo’s Gluten Free All-Purpose Baking Mix</li>
<li>100 grams unsalted butter, softened</li>
<li>125 grams of sugar</li>
<li>2 large eggs</li>
<li>3 tbsp lemon juice</li>
<li>1 tbsp lemon zest</li>
<li>1 tbsp poppy seeds</li>
<li>1 tbsp icing sugar</li>
</ul>
<div align="center">
<hr align="center" noshade="noshade" size="2" width="100%" />
</div>
<p>Directions</p>
<ol>
<li><b>1.    </b>Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. <b></b></li>
<li><b>2.    </b>In a large bowl, beat butter until creamy. Gradually beat in sugar; beat 2 minutes until fluffy. Beat in eggs, gluten free baking mix, lemon juice, lemon zest and poppy seeds, just until smooth.<b></b></li>
<li><b>3.    </b>Pour batter into a greased loaf pan.<b></b></li>
<li><b>4.    </b>Bake 45 minutes. Let cool onto a wire rack. When cold dust with icing sugar.<b></b></li>
</ol>
                                            
                                    
             
	
